<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Primary</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Forest Green — the main call-to-action. Use for the single most important action on a page or section (e.g. Apply, Submit, Book). Limit to one per visual group to preserve hierarchy.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--primary">Primary Button</button>
      <button class="btn btn--primary" disabled>Disabled</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Primary Inverted</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Zingy Yellow on dark backgrounds. Use in place of Primary when the button sits on a dark or image-based surface — hero banners, dark-background sections, or the site footer.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview ds-preview--dark">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--primary-inverted">Primary Inverted</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Secondary</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Paired alongside a Primary button to offer a lower-emphasis alternative (e.g. Learn More next to Apply Now). Never use as a lone CTA when a Primary would be more appropriate. The inverted version follows the same rule on dark surfaces.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--secondary">Secondary</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ds-preview ds-preview--dark">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--secondary-inverted">Secondary Inverted</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Ghost</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Minimal, outline-only button. Use for low-priority or tertiary actions that must exist on-screen without competing with Primary or Secondary buttons — e.g. Cancel, Reset, or a third option in a button group.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--ghost">Ghost Button</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Sizes</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use <strong>Small</strong> inside compact components (cards, table rows, chips). Use <strong>Default</strong> for most contexts. Use <strong>Large</strong> for hero sections or prominent standalone CTAs where extra visual weight aids conversion.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <button class="btn btn--primary btn--sm">Small</button>
      <button class="btn btn--primary">Default</button>
      <button class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Large</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
